                <h2>The Three Pillars</h2>
                <h4>Modeling</h4>
                <p class="paragraph-adjust"> 
                    The basis of modeling is specifically using the mathematical formulas to specify the shape and appearance properties such as the 
                    size, color, texture, and positional parameters. In a sense it is building the form of the image, coming together from the surface or canvas in which it is created on.
                    Some notable modeling software includes Blender, Maya, and Zbrush which allows for developers to create stylized objects for their medium. 
                </p>
                
                <h4>Rendering</h4>
                <p class="paragraph-adjust"> 
                    Rendering is the process where the computer converts the 3D scene or model data into a generative 2D image to be displayed on the screens. Essentially it is like
                    adding the final touches to the canvas by creating the lighting and depthness. Unreal Engine is a popular rendering software for video games and more.
                </p>

                <h4>Animation</h4>
                <p class="paragraph-adjust"> 
                    Animation involves displaying the images with an illusion of motion. It creates life for the image by creating sequences of the images using frames over some time.
                    Some notable animation softwares include Maya and Blender.
                </p>
